2. BERKELEY SPICE3F5
================================================================================

ngspice descends from Berkeley SPICE3f5, the foundational circuit simulator
developed at UC Berkeley over 30+ years. The algorithms for Modified Nodal
Analysis, Newton-Raphson iteration, and the core device model equations
(Shichman-Hodges MOSFET, Gummel-Poon BJT, etc.) originate from this work.

License:  BSD (UC Berkeley)
Authors:  Thomas L. Quarles, A. Richard Newton, Donald O. Pederson,
          Andrei Vladimirescu, and others at UC Berkeley EECS


